# Agent Architecture & Code Generation Rules

## 3-Agent Pipeline (LLM Disabled)

Generation is rule-based. The pipeline is:
1. **StepProcessor** (Agent 1) — classifies raw test steps into `ProcessedStep` with `PageContext` (tracks `currentPage`, `isEditMode`, `currentTab`, `currentApp`)
2. **POMMethodMatcher** (Agent 2) — matches steps to existing POM methods or proposes new ones using `AppSourceIndexer` data
3. **SpecValidator** (Agent 3) — validates generated spec against guardrails, auto-fixes violations (including NAV-001 for missing navigateToBaseUrl)

## Application Source Locators

The `AppSourceIndexer` scans cloned repos (`modetrans/mono.git`, `modetrans/dme.git`) for HTML elements. Cache lives in `src/agent/.cache/`.

### View Mode vs Edit Mode

- **Edit mode**: Form elements exist with exact `#id` — use `page.locator('#id')` with `.inputValue()` / `.fill()`
- **View mode**: Same fields render as plain text in `<td>` — use Playwright chained locators: `page.getByRole('row', { name: /Label/i }).locator('td').nth(1)` with `.textContent()`
- The `StepProcessor` tracks `isEditMode`; `POMMethodMatcher` uses it to choose the locator strategy

## MANDATORY: navigateToBaseUrl() Before Header Navigation

**Detail/form pages** (View Office Info, View Customer, Edit Load, View Carrier, Edit Office, etc.) do NOT render the main navigation header buttons (Admin, Customers, Loads, Finance, Home, etc.).

**Rule**: ALWAYS call `pages.basePage.navigateToBaseUrl()` BEFORE `pages.basePage.hoverOverHeaderByText()`. This is enforced at three levels:
1. **StepMappings** — all HOVER and NAVIGATION entries prepend `navigateToBaseUrl()`
2. **SpecValidator (NAV-001)** — detects and auto-fixes missing `navigateToBaseUrl()` before `hoverOverHeaderByText()`
3. **PromptsConfig guardrail** — `navigateToBaseUrlBeforeHeaderNav` rule flags violations at generation time

The call is idempotent — safe even if already on the base URL. Reference specs: BT-67846, BT-74421, DFB-97746, DFB-97739.

```typescript
// CORRECT — always navigateToBaseUrl before header nav
await pages.basePage.navigateToBaseUrl();
await pages.basePage.hoverOverHeaderByText(HEADERS.CUSTOMER);
await pages.basePage.clickSubHeaderByText(CUSTOMER_SUB_MENU.SEARCH);

// WRONG — will fail if browser is on a detail/form page
await pages.basePage.hoverOverHeaderByText(HEADERS.CUSTOMER);
```

## Assertion Values

Never hardcode expected values in assertions. Use:
- `INVOICE_PROCESS.OFFICE`, `AUTOPAY_STATUS.ENABLED`, `PAYABLE_TOGGLE_VALUE.AGENT`, `FINANCE_MESSAGES.LOAD_NOT_INVOICED` from `globalConstants.ts`
- `testData.*` from CSV for dynamic values (rates, amounts, names)

## POM Method JSDoc

Every new POM method must include: `@author AI Agent`, `@created YYYY-MM-DD`, `@param` (if applicable), `@returns` (if applicable), and locator source reference.
